### 1. Update the `handleToggleBlock` Function in `UserPopUp.jsx`

The `handleToggleBlock` function should be updated to make an API call to either block or unblock the user. After the API call successfully completes, you might want to inform the parent component (`UserManagement.jsx`) about the change to update the UI accordingly. This can be done through a callback function passed down to `UserPopUp` as a prop, say `onUpdateSuccess`.

First, ensure the `updateUser` API method is designed to block or unblock the user based on some parameter, or you have a specific API function for this purpose.

Update `handleToggleBlock` like so:

```jsx
const handleToggleBlock = async () => {
  setIsBlocked(!isBlocked); // Optimistically set the block status
  try {
    const blockStatus = !isBlocked;
    // Assume updateUser is your API call to toggle the block status
    // You might need to adjust it based on your actual API
    await updateUser({ ...editedData, isBlocked: blockStatus }, editedData.id);
    // If success, you may wanna trigger re-fetch or update in the parent component
    if(props.onUpdateSuccess) {
      props.onUpdateSuccess();
    }
  } catch (error) {
    setIsBlocked(isBlocked); // Revert on error
